included.title: Associate Director of Admissions and Student Affairs

included.companyName: University of Michigan - School of Information
included.description:
Designed and implemented enrollment management plan, including recruitment and marketing plan, yield strategies, and retention activities resulting in a 10% increase in matriculation from academic year 2010-2011 to 2011-2012

Maintained new online application for admission and incorporated best practices through active involvement in the university-wide Admissions System Production Group and through developing a strong vendor relationship with the application provider

Evaluated Master of Science in Information (MSI) applications to  make admissions decisions and provided recommendations for merit scholarships, achievement fellowships for underrepresented students of merit, and non-traditional student awards

Directed, assessed, and improved all major events across the student lifecycle including prospective and admitted student events, orientation, enrichment programming for students, and graduation

Managed full-time Student Affairs Program Assistant and 6 part-time student recruiting assistants; provided leadership of this team to most efficiently and effectively leverage the enrollment management plan

Engaged with all SI constituent groups through social media platforms including Facebook, Twitter, Google+, YouTube, Flickr, LinkedIn, blogs, and CTools, the UM Course Management Platform; provided social media leadership and advisement at the university and national level
included.title: Student Affairs Program Manager

included.companyName: University of Michigan - School of Information
included.description:
Oversee enrollment management plan, resulting in a 10% increase in selectivity and a 5% increase in yield from academic year 2011-2012 to 2012-2013 for the Master of Science in Information (MSI) degree.

Direct the admissions process for the PhD, MSI, and Master of Health Informatics, including application creation, data and document handling and policies, timeline for completion, and applicant communication plan.

Oversee the assessment and implementation of all events across the student lifecycle including prospective and admitted student days, orientation, enrichment programming, and graduation

Lead key aspects of student affairs for the PhD and MSI degree programs, including student financials; student life and student group advising; academic advising for the PhD.

Supervisory and training responsibilities for 3 FTE and 7 temporary student workers

Manage budgets related to PhD, Student Life, SI Scholarships, Endowed scholarship accounts, and Recruitment.  Oversee student-related financial needs including policies and practices connecting UM Student Financials with UM Student Financial Aid and our finance team. Oversee financial reimbursements for students including travel, required purchases, and incentive spending.

Chair of the Admission System Production Group, which aims to promote and ensure the effective administration and implementation of recruiting and admissions at U-M.

Created the MSI online application from the ground up, including managing the relationship with the application provider, implementing an extensive test and validation plan, and coordinating with Information Technology Services to verify proper data storage

Assessed programmatic effectiveness and success using online tools such as Zoomerang; implemented change as informed by analysis of survey results
